XII. That for Publique ſatisfaction of the good People of this Nation, ſpeedy conſideration may be had of ſuch Quallifications
for future and ſucceſſive Parliaments, as tend to the Election only of ſuch as are pious and faithfull to the intereſt of the Common-wealth,
to ſit and ſerve as Members in the ſaid Parliament.
